Sentencas: Perovskite oxide La0.6Ca0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-delta (LCFN) has been used in symmetric solid oxide cells (SSOCs) to obtain good electrochemical performance in both fuel cells (SOFCs) and electrolysis cells (SOECs) modes.
Titulo: Tungsten doping La0.6Ca0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ as electrode for highly efficient and stable symmetric solid oxide cells

Sentencas: However, its structural stability still faces challenges and the electrocatalytic activity also needs to be further improved.
Titulo: Tungsten doping La0.6Ca0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ as electrode for highly efficient and stable symmetric solid oxide cells

Sentencas: Herein, tungsten-doped La0.6Ca0.4Fe0.7Ni0.2W0.1O3-delta (LCFNW) perovskite oxide material was synthesized which exhibits good structural stability under H-2 and superior electrochemical performance as an electrode for SSOCs.
Titulo: Tungsten doping La0.6Ca0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ as electrode for highly efficient and stable symmetric solid oxide cells

Sentencas: In SOFCs mode, the cell achieved the maximum power density of 0.58 W.cm(-2) with wet H-2 as fuel at 850 degrees C.
Titulo: Tungsten doping La0.6Ca0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ as electrode for highly efficient and stable symmetric solid oxide cells

Sentencas: In SOECs mode, the current density can reach 1.81 A.cm(-2) for pure CO2 electrolysis at 2 V. Moreover, the SSOCs exhibits outstanding long-term stability in both SOFCs and SOECs modes, proving that doping W in perovskite oxide is an effective strategy to enhance the catalytic activity and stability of the electrode.
Titulo: Tungsten doping La0.6Ca0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ as electrode for highly efficient and stable symmetric solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The LCFNW material developed in this work shows promising prospect as an electrode candidate for SSOCs.
Titulo: Tungsten doping La0.6Ca0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ as electrode for highly efficient and stable symmetric solid oxide cells
